---
title: Carne Asada Tacos All In One Pan
description: There are few things more satisfying than steak for dinner. Until now! These carne-loaded tacos are hearty, filling, and most of all--delicious. Tender bites of seared steak are piled into warm tortillas along with a tangle of veggies, Southwest-spiced crema, and zingy pickled shallot—all topped off with a sprinkle of fresh cilantro. Taco’bout a weeknight win.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/carne-asada-tacos-319d2986.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/carne-asada-tacos-5e5eab2a9d39cd44b710bb67-ee1071d0.pdf
author: Sara Heilman
time required: 25 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 670 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 69 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1160 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/carne-asada-tacos-5e5eab2a9d39cd44b710bb67
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Poblano Pepper{1} into strips. Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Finely chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Shallot{1}. In a #medium bowl{}, combine @White Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, half the shallot, @Sugar{1%tsp} (use 1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings), and @Salt{}. Set aside, stirring occasionally.

> You'll use the rest of the shallot later.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{4%tbsp}, half the @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), and a big pinch of @Salt{}. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in remaining shallot and a big pinch of @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until lightly browned and softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer veggies to a second medium bowl. Wipe out pan.

Pat @Diced Steak{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over high heat. Add steak and season with salt, pepper, and remaining Southwest Spice. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Return veggies to pan; stir until combined. Turn off heat.

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Stir tomato into bowl with pickled shallot.

Divide steak mixture between tortillas. Top with salsa, crema, and cilantro and serve.